props.itemsCount: Total number of items. Pagination uses this value to compute the number of pages to render. It is usually provided by another component that uses pagination for navigation
props.itemsPerPage: Number of items per page. Pagination uses this value to compute the number of pages to render. It is usually provided by another component that uses pagination for navigation. `0` disables pagination (displays only 1 page)
props.maxPages: Maximum number of pages to display. This prop must have value of 3 or more
props.modPage: Style of the single page button
props.modButtons: Style of the next and previous page buttons
props.modDots: Style of the dots separating pages
